                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On June 22, Assistant Secretary of State for Far Eastern Affairs <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWS1">Walter S. Robertson</persName> left Washington National
                    Airport for Korea via <pb facs="0120" n="1238" xml:id="pg_1238"/> Tokyo.
                    Accompanying <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName> were <persName
                        corresp="#p_MCW1">Carl W. McCardle</persName>, Assistant Secretary of State
                    for Public Affairs; <persName corresp="#p_YKT1">Kenneth Young</persName>,
                    Director of the Office of Northeast Asian Affairs; and <persName
                        corresp="#p_CGJL1">General J. Lawton Collins</persName>, Chief of Staff of
                    the United States Army, whose role was to discuss the military situation in
                    Korea. There had been some consideration of having <persName
                        corresp="#p_VFLGJA1">General James Van Fleet</persName>, United States Army
                    (retired), go to Korea with <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName>,
                    but President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>, at the desire
                    of <persName corresp="#p_CGMW1">General Clark</persName>, decided not to send
                        <persName corresp="#p_VFLGJA1">Van Fleet</persName> for the time being.
                    (Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, July 6, 1953, page 14;
                    summary of <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> telephone calls,
                    June 20, 1953, <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> Library,
                        <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> papers,
                        <persName>Whitman</persName> file; telegram <gloss target="#t_DA1"
                        >DA</gloss> 942008, <persName corresp="#p_HGJE1">Hull</persName> to
                        <persName corresp="#p_CGMW1">Clark</persName>, June 22, 1953, <gloss
                        target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss> files, lot 55 D 338)</p>
                <p>While in Korea <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName>, as President
                        <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>’s personal envoy, used the
                    communication channels available in Seoul; therefore telegrams from him carry
                    his bracketed signature rather than that of Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_BEO1">Briggs</persName>.</p>
